cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is about developing a neural conversation model that combines retrieval-based and generation-based methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and knowledge grounding, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
